File: Bavelile Hlongwa, who was appointed to her position in May, was deputy chairperson of the NYDA and an NEC member of the now-defunct ANCYL. JOHANNESBURG - Deputy Minister of Energy and Mineral Resources Bavelile Hlongwa will be laid to rest in Durban, KwaZulu-Natal, today, on Saturday. She was killed in a car accident last week Friday in Limpopo. READ: Condolences pour in for Hlongwa Hlongwa had stopped to help a motorist whose car had overturned and was hit by a truck. READ: Deputy Mineral Resources Minister Bavelile Hlongwa dies President Cyril Ramaphosa has declared an official funeral and ordered that the national flag flies at half-mast. He's expected to deliver the eulogy at Hlongwa's funeral.